# nflfastR

## At 03:00 in January, February, and every month from September through December.
0 3 * 1,2,9-12 * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-plays-nflfastr.mjs -d >> /var/log/league/league-import-plays-nflfastr.log 2>&1

## At 04:00 in January, February and every month from September through December.
0 3 * 1,2,9-12 * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-nfl-games-nflverse-nfldata.mjs -d >> /var/log/league/league-import-nfl-games-nflverse-nfldata.log 2>&1

## Every Tuesday at 07:15 in January, February, and September through December.
## nflverse weekly_rosters releases land late Monday; this populates
## player_gamelogs.active=false for game-day inactives and reserve-list members.
## Restores the signal lost when commit 84c52f63 removed import-player-gamelogs.mjs.
15 7 * 1,2,9-12 2 NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-nflverse-weekly-rosters.mjs --force_download >> /var/log/league/import-nflverse-weekly-rosters.log 2>&1

## Every Tuesday at 07:00 in January, February, and September through December.
## nflverse injuries releases land late Monday; this populates player_changelog
## with source='nflverse' as Sleeper redundancy. Failover signal: if the 2022
## Sleeper blackout recurs, this keeps the historical injury index warm with
## at most one week of lag. Does NOT pass --write_practice -- Rotowire owns
## 2020+ practice writes; nflverse practice backfill is pre-2020 only.
0 7 * 1,2,9-12 2 NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-nflverse-injuries.mjs --force_download >> /var/log/league/import-nflverse-injuries.log 2>&1

## Every Tuesday at 09:00 in January, February, and September through December.
## Rebuilds the historical_injury_index for the current season. Runs after
## update-player-gamelog-ruled-out-status (5am), import-gameday-rosters (5am),
## import-nflverse-weekly-rosters (7:15am), and import-nflverse-injuries (7:00am)
## so all upstream signals are fresh.
##
## January and February runs target the new calendar year and are intentionally
## no-ops until Week 1 of the new season; the prior season's final refresh
## happens in the previous December run.
0 9 * 1,2,9-12 2 NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/generate-historical-injury-index.mjs --year $(date +\%Y) >> /var/log/league/generate-historical-injury-index.log 2>&1

## NFL.com FDL players (sources player_changelog.nfl_status: IR/PUP/SUSP/NFI/DID_NOT_REPORT)
## 3:30am daily plus game-day 12:15/17:10/20:00 in-season.  Mirrors Sleeper cadence.
30 3 * * * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-players-nfl.mjs >> /var/log/league/import-players-nfl.log 2>&1
15 12 * 1,2,9-12 * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-players-nfl.mjs >> /var/log/league/import-players-nfl.log 2>&1
10 17 * 1,2,9-12 * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-players-nfl.mjs >> /var/log/league/import-players-nfl.log 2>&1
0 20 * 1,2,9-12 * NODE_ENV=production /root/.nvm/versions/node/current/bin/node /root/league/scripts/import-players-nfl.mjs >> /var/log/league/import-players-nfl.log 2>&1



